    "summary": "Following the fall of the Gupta Empire, King Harsha Vardhana of Kannauj unified northern India and established a reign of peace and cultural revival. Harsha was a patron of literature and a writer himself, composing three famous Sanskrit plays. Explore the historical details, ecological connections, and scientific breakthroughs that define this unique aspect of Indian civilization.",
